geneVariantDescriptions.description: TP53 over exp indicates an over expression of the Tp53 protein. However, the mechanism causing the over expression is unspecified.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a Phase I trial, the HLA-A2 p53:264-272 vaccine demonstrated safety and preliminary efficacy in patients with TP53 overexpressing ovarian cancer, resulting in a progression-free survival of 5.5 months and an overall survival of 40.4 months (PMID: 21927947).

references.title: A gynecologic oncology group phase II trial of two p53 peptide vaccine approaches: subcutaneous injection and intravenous pulsed dendritic cells in high recurrence risk ovarian cancer patients.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, Erivedge (vismodegib) inhibited cell growth, induced apoptosis in tumor cells derived from spontaneous medulloblastoma of heterozygous PTCH1 knockout mice which also harbored TP53 over expression in culture (PMID: 26130651).
